-- B&M shares rise 5 percent above float price in conditional deals
-- 
-- Thu Jun 12, 2014 03:21AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, June 12 (Reuters) - Shares in British discount retailer B&M <BMEB.L> rose 5 percent above its listing price of 270 pence a share on Thursday in conditional deals, valuing the group at more than 2.8 billion pounds ($4.7 billion).

The shares were trading at 284 pence at 0713 GMT. Selling shareholders the Arora family and U.S. private equity firm Clayton, Dubilier & Rice will receive 1.01 billion pounds of gross proceeds from the sale of 40 of the company's equity, assuming no exercise of an over-allotment option, it said.